Custom property | Description | Default

`--api-type-document-type-attribute-color` | Color of each attribute that describes a property | `#616161`
`--api-type-document-examples-title-color` | Color of examples section title | ``
`--api-type-document-examples-border-color` | Example section border color | `transparent`
`--code-background-color` | Background color of the examples section | ``
`--arc-font-body1` | Mixin applied to an example name label | `{}`
`--arc-font-body2` | Mixin applied to the examples section title | `{}`

elements.description:
`property-shape-document`

Renders a documentation for a shape property of AMF model.

## Styling

`<property-shape-document>` provides the following custom properties and mixins for styling:

Custom property | Description | Default
----------------|-------------|----------
`--property-shape-document` | Mixin applied to this elment | `{}`
`--property-shape-document-array-color` | Property border color when type is an array | `#8BC34A`
`--property-shape-document-object-color` | Property border color when type is an object | `#FF9800`
`--property-shape-document-union-color` | Property border color when type is an union | `#FFEB3B`
`--arc-font-subhead` | Theme mixin, applied to the property title | `{}`
`--property-shape-document-title` | Mixin applied to the property title | `{}`
`--api-type-document-property-parent-color` | Color of the parent property label | `#757575`
`--api-type-document-property-color` | Color of the property name label when display name is used | `#757575`
`--api-type-document-child-docs-margin-left` | Margin left of item's properties description relative to the title when the item is a child of another property | `24px`
`--api-type-document-type-color` | Color of the "type" trait | `white`
`--api-type-document-type-background-color` | Background color of the "type" trait | `#2196F3`
`--api-type-document-trait-background-color` | Background color to main range trait (type name) | `#EEEEEE`,
`--api-type-document-trait-border-radius` | Border radious of a main property traits | `3px`
`--api-type-document-property-name-width` | Width of the left hand side column with property name | `240px`

Computed value, true if this propery contains a complex

elements.description:
`api-type-document`

An element that recuresively renders a documentation for a data type
using from model.

Pass AMF's shape type `property` array to render the documentation.

## Styling

`<api-type-document>` provides the following custom properties and mixins for styling:

Custom property | Description | Default
----------------|-------------|----------
`--api-type-document` | Mixin applied to this elment | `{}`
`--api-type-document-union-button-background-color` | Background color of union selector button | `#fff`
`--api-type-document-union-button-color` | Color of union selector button | `#000`
`--api-type-document-union-button-active-background-color` | Background color of active union selector button | `#CDDC39`
`--api-type-document-union-button-active-color` | Color of active union selector button | `#000`

From `property-shape-document`

Custom property | Description | Default
----------------|-------------|----------
`--property-shape-document` | Mixin applied each proeprty element | `{}`
`--property-shape-document-array-color` | Property border color when type is an array | `#8BC34A`
`--property-shape-document-object-color` | Property border color when type is an object | `#FF9800`
`--property-shape-document-union-color` | Property border color when type is an union | `#FFEB3B`
`--arc-font-subhead` | Theme mixin, applied to the property title | `{}`
`--property-shape-document-title` | Mixin applied to the property title | `{}`
`--api-type-document-property-parent-color` | Color of the parent property label | `#757575`
`--api-type-document-property-color` | Color of the property name label when display name is used | `#757575`
`--api-type-document-child-docs-margin-left` | Margin left of the item's properties description relative to the title when the item is a child property of another property | `24px`
`--api-type-document-type-color` | Color of the "type" trait | `white`
`--api-type-document-type-background-color` | Background color of the "type" trait | `#2196F3`
`--api-type-document-trait-background-color` | Background color to main range trait (type, required, enum) | `#EEEEEE`,
`--api-type-document-trait-border-radius` | Border radious of a main property traits like type, required, enum | `3px`

From `property-range-document`

Custom property | Description | Default
----------------|-------------|----------
`--property-range-document` | Mixin applied to this elment | `{}`
`--api-type-document-type-attribute-color` | Color of each attribute that describes a property | `#616161`
`--api-type-document-examples-title-color` | Color of examples section title | ``
`--api-type-document-examples-border-color` | Example section border color | `transparent`
`--code-background-color` | Background color of the examples section | ``
`--arc-font-body1` | Mixin applied to an example name label | `{}`
`--arc-font-body2` | Mixin applied to the examples section title | `{}`

properties.name: amfModel
properties.description:
Generated AMF json/ld model form the API spec.
The element assumes the object of the first array item to be a
type of `"http://raml.org/vocabularies/document#Document`
on AMF vocabulary.

It is only usefult for the element to resolve references.

properties.name: shape
properties.description: A property shape definition of AMF.

properties.name: range
properties.description: Computes value of shape's http://raml.org/vocabularies/shapes#range

properties.name: mediaType
properties.description:
Media type to use to render examples.
If not set a "raw" version of the example from API spec file is used.

properties.name: noExamplesActions
properties.description: When set it removes actions bar from the examples render.

properties.name: ns
properties.description: A namespace for AMF model

properties.name: aware
properties.description: `raml-aware` scope property to use.

properties.name: type
properties.description:
A type definition to render.
This should be a one of the following AMF types:

- `http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#NodeShape` (Object)
- `http://raml.org/vocabularies/shapes#UnionShape` (Union)
- `http://raml.org/vocabularies/shapes#ArrayShape` (Array)
- `http://raml.org/vocabularies/shapes#ScalarShape` (single property)

It also accepts array of properties like list of headers or
parameters.

properties.name: _resolvedType
properties.description: The type after it has been resolved.

properties.name: parentTypeName
properties.description:
Should be set if described properties has a parent type.
This is used when recursively iterating over properties.

properties.name: hasParentType
properties.description: Computed value, true if the shape has parent type.

properties.name: isScalar
properties.description: True if given `type` is a scalar property

properties.name: isArray
properties.description: True if given `type` is an array property

properties.name: isObject
properties.description: True if given `type` is an object property

properties.name: isUnion
properties.description: True if given `type` is an union property

properties.name: isAnd
properties.description: True if given `type` is OAS "and" type.

properties.name: unionTypes
properties.description:
Computed list of union type types to render in union type
selector.
Each item has `label` and `isScalar` property.

properties.name: andTypes
properties.description: List of types definition and name for OAS' "and" type

properties.name: selectedUnion
properties.description: Selected index of union type in `unionTypes` array.

properties.name: narrow
properties.description:
A property to set when the component is rendered in the narrow
view. To be used with mobile rendering or when the
components occupies only small part of the screen.

properties.name: noMainExample
properties.description: When set an example in this `type` object won't be rendered even if set.

methods.name: _computeRangeDataType
methods.description: Computes type from a `http://raml.org/vocabularies/shapes#range` object

methods.name: _computeRange
methods.description: Computes value for `range` property.

methods.name: _computeArrayProperties
methods.description: Computes properties to render Array items documentation.

methods.name: _computeIsUnion
methods.description:
Computes value for `isUnion` property.
Union type is identified as a `http://raml.org/vocabularies/shapes#UnionShape`
type.

methods.name: _computeIsObject
methods.description:
Computes value for `isObject` property.
Object type is identified as a `http://raml.org/vocabularies/shapes#NodeShape`
type.

methods.name: _computeIsArray
methods.description:
Computes value for `isArray` property.
Array type is identified as a `http://raml.org/vocabularies/shapes#ArrayShape`
type.

methods.name: _computeUnionTypes
methods.description: Computes list of union type labels to render.

methods.name: _computeArrayUnionLabel
methods.description: Computes union type label when the union is in Array.

params.name: items
params.description: Array's items property or a single property

methods.name: _computeDisplayName
methods.description: Computes name label for the shape.

methods.name: _getAmfKey
methods.description: Returns compact model key for given value.

return.desc:
Compact model property name or the same value if
value not found in the context.

methods.name: _ensureAmfModel
methods.description: Ensures that the model is AMF object.

methods.name: _ensureArray
methods.description:
Ensures that the value is an array.
It returns undefined when there's no value.
It returns the same array if the value is already an array.
It returns new array of the item is not an array.

methods.name: _getValue
methods.description: Gets a signle scalar value from a model.

params.name: model
params.description: Amf model to extract the value from.

params.name: key
params.description: Model key to search for the value

methods.name: _getValueArray
methods.description: Gets values from a model as an array of `@value` properties.

params.name: model
params.description: Amf model to extract the value from.

params.name: key
params.description: Model key to search for the value

methods.name: _hasType
methods.description: Checks if a model has a type.

return.desc: True if model has a type.

methods.name: _hasProperty
methods.description: Checks if a shape has a property.

methods.name: _computePropertyArray
methods.description: Computes array value of a property in a model (shape).

methods.name: _computePropertyObject
methods.description:
Computes a value of a property in a model (shape).
It takes first value of a property, if exists.

methods.name: _computeHasStringValue
methods.description: Tests if a passed argumet exists.

methods.name: _computeHasArrayValue
methods.description:
Computes if passed argument is an array and has a value.
It does not check for type or value of the array items.

methods.name: _computeDescription
methods.description: Computes description for a shape.

methods.name: _computeServerVariables
methods.description: Computes value for `serverVariables` property.

methods.name: _computeEndpointVariables
methods.description: Computes value for `endpointVariables` property.

methods.name: _computePayload
methods.description: Computes value for the `payload` property

methods.name: _computeReturns
methods.description: Computes value for `returns` property

methods.name: _computeSecurity
methods.description: Computes value for `security` property

methods.name: _computeHasCustomProperties
methods.description: Computes value for `hasCustomProperties` property.

methods.name: _computeApiVersion
methods.description: Computes API version from the AMF model.

methods.name: _computeEncodes
methods.description: Computes model's `encodes` property.

methods.name: _computeDeclares
methods.description: Computes list of declarations in the AMF api model.

params.name: model
params.description: AMF json/ld model for an API

methods.name: _computeReferences
methods.description: Computes list of references in the AMF api model.

params.name: model
params.description: AMF json/ld model for an API

methods.name: _computeWebApi
methods.description: Computes AMF's `http://schema.org/WebAPI` model

params.name: model
params.description: AMF json/ld model for an API

methods.name: _computeServer
methods.description: Computes value for `server` property that is later used with other computations.

methods.name: _computeEndpointUri
methods.description: Computes endpoint's URI based on `amfModel` and `endpoint` models.

methods.name: _getBaseUri
methods.description:
Computes base URI value from either `baseUri`, `iron-meta` with
`ApiBaseUri` key or `amfModel` value (in this order).

return.desc: Base uri value. Can be empty string.

methods.name: _getAmfBaseUri
methods.description: Computes base URI from AMF model.

params.name: protocols
params.description:
Listy of supporte dprotocols. If not
provided and required to compute the url it uses `amfModel` to compute
protocols

methods.name: _ensureUrlScheme
methods.description:
A function that makes sure that the URL has a scheme definition.
If no supported protocols information is available it assumes `http`.

params.name: protocols
params.description:
List of supported by the API protocols
An array of string like: `['HTTP', 'HTTPS']`. It lowercase the value.
If not set it tries to read supported protocols value from `amfModel`
property.

methods.name: _computeProtocols
methods.description: Computes supported protocols by the API.

methods.name: _computeExpects
methods.description: Computes value for the `expects` property.

methods.name: _computePropertyValue
methods.description:
Tries to find an example value (whether it's default value or from an
example) to put it into snippet's values.

methods.name: _computeEndpoints
methods.description: Computes list of endpoints from a WebApi model.

return.desc: Always returns an array of endpoints.

methods.name: _computeEndpointModel
methods.description: Computes model for an endpoint documentation.

methods.name: _computeEndpointByPath
methods.description: Computes model for an endpoint documentation using it's path.

methods.name: _computeMethodModel
methods.description: Computes method for the method documentation.

methods.name: _computeOperations
methods.description: Computes list of operations in an endpoint

methods.name: _computeMethodEndpoint
methods.description: Computes an endpoint for a method.

methods.name: __computeMethodsListForMethod
methods.description:
Computes a list of methods for an endpoint that contains a method with
given id.

return.desc: A list of sibling methods or undefined.

methods.name: _computeType
methods.description: Computes a type documentation model.

methods.name: _computeReferenceType
methods.description: Computes a type model from a reference (library for example).

params.name: reference
params.description: AMF model for a reference to extract the data from

return.desc: Type definition or undefined if not found.

methods.name: _computeSecurityModel
methods.description: Computes model for selected security definition.

methods.name: _computeDocument
methods.description: Computes a documentation model.

methods.name: _resolve
methods.description: Resolves a reference to an external fragment.

methods.name: _getExampleValue
methods.description: Gets string value for an example data model.

params.name: isJson
params.description:
If set it checks if the `raw` value is valid JSON.
If it isn't then it parses structured value.

methods.name: _computeExampleFromStructuredValue
methods.description: Computes an example from example structured value.

return.desc: Javascript object or array with structured value.

methods.name: _computeStructuredExampleValue
methods.description: Computes value with propert data type for a structured example.

methods.name: __typeChanged
methods.description:
Called when resolved type or amfModel changed.
Creates a debouncer to compute UI values so it's independent of
order of assigning properties.

methods.name: _typeChanged
methods.description: Handles type change. Sets basic view control properties.

methods.name: _computeArrayParentName
methods.description: Computes parent name for the array type table.

return.desc: Parent type name of refault value for array type.

methods.name: _unionTypesChanged
methods.description: Resets union selection when union types list changes.

methods.name: _selectUnion
methods.description:
Handler for union type button click.
Sets `selectedUnion` property.

methods.name: _unionTypeActive
methods.description: Computes if selectedUnion equals current item index.

methods.name: _computeUnionProperty
methods.description: Computes properties for union type.

methods.name: _computeProperties
methods.description:
Helper function for the view. Extracts `http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#property`
from the shape model

methods.name: _computeAndTypes
methods.description: Computes list values for `andTypes` property.

return.desc: An array of type definitions and label to render
